item.description:
Now that we have Modlishka up and running. Let&rsquo;s get it configured with a target login provider. We&rsquo;ll use Authentik to get an okta like experience.
sudo apt-get install -y pwgen mkdir ~/Desktop/op/docker/authentik cd ~/Desktop/op/docker/ echo &#34;PG_PASS=$(pwgen -s 40 1)&#34; &gt;&gt; .env echo &#34;AUTHENTIK_SECRET_KEY=$(pwgen -s 50 1)&#34; &gt;&gt; .env echo &#34;AUTHENTIK_ERROR_REPORTING__ENABLED=true&#34; &gt;&gt; .env Add the follow for emails&hellip;
# SMTP Host Emails are sent to AUTHENTIK_EMAIL__HOST=mailhog AUTHENTIK_EMAIL__PORT=1025 # Optionally authenticate (don&#39;t add quotation marks to your password) AUTHENTIK_EMAIL__USERNAME= AUTHENTIK_EMAIL__PASSWORD= # Use StartTLS AUTHENTIK_EMAIL__USE_TLS=false # Use SSL AUTHENTIK_EMAIL__USE_SSL=false AUTHENTIK_EMAIL__TIMEOUT=10 # Email address authentik will send from, should have a correct @domain AUTHENTIK_EMAIL__FROM=authentik@target.
